Note:
This file handles Bifrost graph node definitions for accelerator compilation.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process Bifrost node type definitions and high-level operations
- Handle operation nodes (MatrixMultiply, Convolve2D, FFT, etc.)
- Manage data nodes and tensor types
- Process node attribute storage and metadata

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Bifrost nodes represent high-level accelerator operations
- Proper node abstraction enables cross-accelerator optimization
- Node definitions are foundation for Bifrost graph representation

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- BifrostNode type definitions and operation types
- High-level operation nodes (matrix ops, convolutions, FFT)
- Data tensor nodes with shape and type information
- Node metadata and attribute management

This is v0.8.5 Bifrost implementation - Production-grade complete
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Definitions - Bifrost Type System
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
BifrostType represents hardware-aware types for accelerators.
Unlike MIR/LIR which use basic primitives, Bifrost types directly map to
accelerator capabilities: vectors, matrices, tensors, textures, fixed-point.

Type hierarchy:
- Primitive: Basic scalar types (Int8/16/32/64, Float16/32/64)
- FixedPoint: DSP/FPGA fixed-point arithmetic (total_bits, fractional_bits)
- Vector: SIMD vector types (element_type, size)
- Matrix: Linear algebra types (element_type, rows, cols)
- Texture: GPU texture types (format, dimensions)
- Tensor: Neural network tensor types (element_type, shape)

Memory layout (OWNED HEAP Tier 3):
Each type variant stored with discriminant + variant-specific data
@End Reasoning

Note: Bifrost type tag constants (discriminates between variants)
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_PRIMITIVE as Integer is 0
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_FIXED_POINT as Integer is 1
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_VECTOR as Integer is 2
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_MATRIX as Integer is 3
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_TEXTURE as Integer is 4
Constant BIFROST_TYPE_TENSOR as Integer is 5

Type called "BifrostType":
    tag as Integer
    field_a as Integer
    field_b as Integer
    field_c as Integer
End Type

Note: Primitive type kind constants
Constant BIFROST_INT8 as Integer is 1
Constant BIFROST_INT16 as Integer is 2
Constant BIFROST_INT32 as Integer is 3
Constant BIFROST_INT64 as Integer is 4
Constant BIFROST_UINT8 as Integer is 5
Constant BIFROST_UINT16 as Integer is 6
Constant BIFROST_UINT32 as Integer is 7
Constant BIFROST_UINT64 as Integer is 8
Constant BIFROST_FLOAT16 as Integer is 9
Constant BIFROST_FLOAT32 as Integer is 10
Constant BIFROST_FLOAT64 as Integer is 11

Note: Texture format constants
Constant TEX_FORMAT_RGBA8 as Integer is 1
Constant TEX_FORMAT_RGBA16F as Integer is 2
Constant TEX_FORMAT_RGBA32F as Integer is 3
Constant TEX_FORMAT_R8 as Integer is 4
Constant TEX_FORMAT_R16F as Integer is 5
Constant TEX_FORMAT_R32F as Integer is 6

@Reasoning
OpKind represents high-level semantic operations for accelerators.
Unlike MIR which uses low-level add/mul/load, Bifrost uses operations
that directly map to accelerator capabilities:
- MatrixMultiply maps to GPU tensor cores, FPGA systolic arrays
- Convolve2D maps to GPU texture units, FPGA conv engines
- FFT maps to DSP FFT hardware, GPU FFT kernels

This abstraction enables cross-platform optimization without losing
semantic meaning of the computation.
@End Reasoning

Type OpKind is:
    | Add
    | Subtract
    | MulOp
    | DivOp
    | ModOp
    | Negate
    | MatrixMultiply
    | MatrixAdd
    | MatrixTranspose
    | MatrixInverse
    | VectorDot
    | VectorCross
    | VectorNorm
    | Convolve2D
    | Convolve3D
    | FFT
    | IFFT
    | FIR_Filter
    | IIR_Filter
    | Blur
    | Sharpen
    | EdgeDetect
    | ColorConvert
    | Resize
    | Rotate
    | ReLU
    | Sigmoid
    | Tanh
    | Softmax
    | BatchNorm
    | LayerNorm
    | ConvLayer
    | PoolingLayer
    | FullyConnected
    | Load
    | Store
    | LoadTexture
    | StoreTexture
    | ReduceSum
    | ReduceMax
    | ReduceMin
    | ReduceMean
    | Equal
    | NotEqual
    | LessThan
    | LessEqual
    | GreaterThan
    | GreaterEqual
    | And
    | Or
    | Xor
    | Not
    | BitwiseAnd
    | BitwiseOr
    | BitwiseXor
    | BitwiseNot
    | ShiftLeft
    | ShiftRight
    | Cast
    | Bitcast
    | FloatToInt
    | IntToFloat
    | Select
    | Clamp
    | Mix
    | Step
    | SmoothStep
    | Pad
    | Tile
    | Reshape
End Type

@Reasoning
ParallelismKind defines execution model for accelerators.
Each kind maps to specific hardware capabilities:
- DataParallel: GPU threads, CPU SIMD, FPGA parallel paths
- TaskGraph: Multi-core CPU, GPU streams, FPGA task pipelines
- Pipeline: FPGA pipeline stages, DSP streaming, GPU compute pipelines
- SIMD: CPU vector units, GPU warp-level operations
@End Reasoning

Type ParallelismKind is:
    | DataParallel
    | TaskGraph
    | Pipeline
    | SIMD
End Type

@Reasoning
MemorySpace defines where data resides on accelerator.
Critical for performance as memory hierarchy has 100x+ speed differences:
- Global: Main device memory (slow, large capacity)
- Shared: Fast scratchpad (GPU shared memory, FPGA block RAM)
- Local: Thread-local registers (GPU registers, CPU cache)
- Constant: Read-only broadcast memory (GPU constant cache)
@End Reasoning

Type MemorySpace is:
    | Global
    | Shared
    | Local
    | ConstantValue
End Type

@Reasoning
BifrostNode represents computational nodes in the Bifrost DAG.
Four node types:
- Constant: Compile-time known values
- Input: Data flowing into graph (from CPU or external source)
- Output: Data flowing out of graph (to CPU or external sink)
- Operation: Computational transformation

Memory layout (OWNED HEAP Tier 3):
Each node variant stored with discriminant + variant data
Operation nodes store list of input edge references (not direct node pointers)
@End Reasoning

Type BifrostNode is:
    | Constant as value as Integer, type as Integer
    | Input as name as Integer, type as Integer, memory_space as MemorySpace
    | Output as name as Integer, type as Integer, memory_space as MemorySpace
    | Operation as op as OpKind, inputs as Integer, output_type as Integer, parallelism as ParallelismKind, metadata as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type System Functions - Complete Production-Grade Implementations
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
create_primitive_type allocates a primitive scalar type.
Maps Runa integer/float types to Bifrost accelerator types.
Returns pointer to allocated BifrostType in OWNED HEAP.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates 16 bytes on the OWNED HEAP. Writes BIFROST_TYPE_PRIMITIVE (0) as
the discriminant at offset 0 and the primitive kind value at offset 8.
Returns the type pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one heap allocation plus two 64-bit stores. Caches well; called once
per literal scalar type in the lowering pipeline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation; caller owns the returned type pointer. No capability
requirements.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_primitive_type" that takes kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure (discriminant + data)
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(16)

    Note: Set discriminant to Primitive (variant 0)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 0)

    Note: Set primitive kind
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, kind)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_fixed_point_type creates DSP/FPGA fixed-point type.
Fixed-point arithmetic trades dynamic range for deterministic performance.
Common in DSP (16-bit audio), FPGA (custom bit widths), embedded systems.
Example: Fixed with 16 total / 8 fractional bits has range [-128, 127.996]
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Validates total_bits > 0, fractional_bits >= 0, and fractional_bits <=
total_bits; returns 0 (null) on any failure. Allocates 24 bytes, writes
BIFROST_TYPE_FIXED_POINT (1) at offset 0, total_bits at offset 8, and
fractional_bits at offset 16. Returns the type pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - three branches plus one heap allocation and three stores. Off the
hot path; only invoked when DSP/FPGA fixed-point types are introduced.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. Width validation prevents oversized or inconsistent
bit-width configurations that would crash downstream codegen.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_fixed_point_type" that takes total_bits as Integer, fractional_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate bit widths
    If total_bits is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If fractional_bits is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If fractional_bits is greater than total_bits:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(24)

    Note: Set discriminant to FixedPoint (variant 1)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 1)

    Note: Set total bits and fractional bits
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, total_bits)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 16, fractional_bits)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_vector_type creates SIMD vector type.
Vectors enable data-parallel operations - a 4-lane float32 vector processes
4 floats simultaneously. Maps to CPU SIMD (SSE, AVX, NEON), GPU vector
operations, FPGA parallel datapaths.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null element_type or non-positive size. Validates size is a
power of 2 via (size AND (size-1)) == 0; rejects on failure. Allocates 24
bytes, writes BIFROST_TYPE_VECTOR (2) at offset 0, element_type pointer at
offset 8, and size at offset 16. Returns the type pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - a few branches plus one allocation and three stores.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. Power-of-two enforcement keeps the vector type
hardware-realisable; element_type is borrowed (caller owns it).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_vector_type" that takes element_type as Integer, size as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate element type exists
    If element_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate size is positive power of 2 (hardware requirement)
    If size is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if size is power of 2
    Let is_power_of_2 be 0
    If size bitwise_and (size minus 1) is equal to 0:
        Set is_power_of_2 to 1
    End If

    If is_power_of_2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(24)

    Note: Set discriminant to Vector (variant 2)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 2)

    Note: Set element type pointer and size
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, element_type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 16, size)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_matrix_type creates linear algebra matrix type.
Matrices enable efficient GPU tensor core operations, FPGA systolic arrays.
A 4x4 matrix of float32 is a common graphics transformation type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if element_type is null or rows / cols are non-positive. Allocates
32 bytes, writes BIFROST_TYPE_MATRIX (3) at offset 0, element_type pointer
at offset 8, rows at offset 16, cols at offset 24. Returns the type pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one allocation, four stores.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. element_type is borrowed; dimensions are scalars and
need no validation here beyond positivity.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_matrix_type" that takes element_type as Integer, rows as Integer, cols as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate element type exists
    If element_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate dimensions are positive
    If rows is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If cols is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(32)

    Note: Set discriminant to Matrix (variant 3)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 3)

    Note: Set element type, rows, and columns
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, element_type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 16, rows)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 24, cols)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_texture_type creates GPU texture sampler type.
Textures provide specialized memory layout and hardware interpolation.
Critical for graphics, image processing, and convolutional neural networks.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if format <= 0 or dimensions not in [1..3] (covers 1D, 2D, 3D).
Allocates 24 bytes, writes BIFROST_TYPE_TEXTURE (4) at offset 0, format at
offset 8, dimensions at offset 16. Returns the type pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. Dimension range check prevents invalid texture
configurations that the GPU backend cannot lower.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_texture_type" that takes format as Integer, dimensions as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate format is known
    If format is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate dimensions (1D, 2D, 3D, Cube)
    If dimensions is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    If dimensions is greater than 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(24)

    Note: Set discriminant to Texture (variant 4)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 4)

    Note: Set format and dimensions
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, format)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 16, dimensions)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_tensor_type creates multi-dimensional array type for neural networks.
Tensors generalize matrices to N dimensions (e.g. batch, height, width,
channels). Essential for deep learning inference on GPUs, TPUs, NPUs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if element_type or shape is null, or if shape has zero length.
Iterates shape entries and returns 0 if any dimension is non-positive.
Allocates 24 bytes, writes BIFROST_TYPE_TENSOR (5) at offset 0, element_type
pointer at offset 8, shape list pointer at offset 16. Returns the type
pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(rank) for the per-dimension validation loop; otherwise O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. element_type and shape List are borrowed; shape is
not copied, so callers must not mutate it after this call or the tensor
type will see the mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_tensor_type" that takes element_type as Integer, shape as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate element type exists
    If element_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate shape list exists and has elements
    If shape is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let shape_len be List.length(shape)
    If shape_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate all dimensions are positive
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than shape_len:
        Let dim be List.get(shape, i)
        If dim is less than or equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Allocate BifrostType structure
    Let type_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(24)

    Note: Set discriminant to Tensor (variant 5)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 0, 5)

    Note: Set element type and shape list pointer
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 8, element_type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(type_ptr, 16, shape)

    Return type_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
get_type_size_bytes calculates memory size in bytes for a BifrostType.
Must handle all type variants recursively (vectors contain element types,
etc.). Size calculation is critical for memory allocation, bandwidth
estimation, and cache analysis.

Variant-specific rules:
- Primitive: Map kind to byte size (Int8=1, Int32=4, Float32=4, Float64=8)
- FixedPoint: (total_bits + 7) divided by 8 to round up to byte boundary
- Vector: element_size times vector_size
- Matrix: element_size times rows times cols
- Texture: Format-dependent (RGBA8=4 bytes/pixel, RGBA32F=16 bytes/pixel)
- Tensor: element_size times product of dimensions
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null type. Reads the discriminant at offset 0 and dispatches:
discriminant 0 (Primitive) reads kind at offset 8 and returns the matched
byte width or 0 on unknown kind; discriminant 1 (FixedPoint) returns
(total_bits+7) divided by 8; discriminant 2 (Vector) reads the element_type
pointer and multiplies its size by the lane count; discriminant 3 (Matrix)
multiplies element size by rows times cols; discriminant 4 (Texture) reads
format and dispatches per known formats; discriminant 5 (Tensor) multiplies
element size by the product of every dimension in the shape list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) for primitives; O(rank) for tensors due to the shape walk. Recursion
depth equals type nesting depth (typically 1-2).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read on type metadata; no allocation, no syscalls.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_type_size_bytes" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if type pointer is valid
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get type discriminant to determine variant
    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)

    Note: Primitive type - map kind to byte size
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)

        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT8:
            Return 1
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT16:
            Return 2
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT32:
            Return 4
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT64:
            Return 8
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT8:
            Return 1
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT16:
            Return 2
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT32:
            Return 4
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT64:
            Return 8
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT16:
            Return 2
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT32:
            Return 4
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT64:
            Return 8
        End If

        Note: Unknown primitive kind
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: FixedPoint type - round up to byte boundary
    If discriminant is equal to 1:
        Let total_bits be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let size_bytes be (total_bits plus 7) divided by 8
        Return size_bytes
    End If

    Note: Vector type - element size multiplied by vector size
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Let element_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let size be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)

        Let element_size be get_type_size_bytes(element_type)
        If element_size is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Return element_size multiplied by size
    End If

    Note: Matrix type - element size multiplied by rows multiplied by cols
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Set element_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let rows be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Let cols be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 24)

        Set element_size to get_type_size_bytes(element_type)
        If element_size is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Return element_size multiplied by rows multiplied by cols
    End If

    Note: Texture type - format dependent
    If discriminant is equal to 4:
        Let format be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)

        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_RGBA8:
            Return 4
        End If
        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_RGBA16F:
            Return 8
        End If
        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_RGBA32F:
            Return 16
        End If
        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_R8:
            Return 1
        End If
        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_R16F:
            Return 2
        End If
        If format is equal to TEX_FORMAT_R32F:
            Return 4
        End If

        Note: Unknown texture format
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Tensor type - element size multiplied by product of dimensions
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Set element_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let shape be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)

        Set element_size to get_type_size_bytes(element_type)
        If element_size is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Calculate product of all dimensions
        Let shape_len be List.length(shape)
        Let total_elements be 1

        Let i be 0
        While i is less than shape_len:
            Let dim be List.get(shape, i)
            Set total_elements to total_elements multiplied by dim
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return element_size multiplied by total_elements
    End If

    Note: Unknown type discriminant
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
get_type_alignment calculates required memory alignment for a type.
Alignment is critical for performance - misaligned access causes penalties
or crashes. Hardware requirements:
- Scalars: align to their size (Float32 = 4-byte aligned)
- Vectors: align to vector size (a 4-lane float32 = 16-byte aligned)
- Matrices: align to row size
- Tensors: align to element size
Algorithm mirrors get_type_size_bytes but returns alignment requirements.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null type. Reads the discriminant. For Primitive and FixedPoint,
delegates to get_type_size_bytes (alignment equals size). For Vector,
fetches vector size and clamps to 16 (typical SIMD alignment cap). For
Matrix, returns the element size (conservative row-stride alignment). For
Texture, returns 4 (standard texel alignment). For Tensor, returns the
element size. Unknown discriminants return 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) for most variants; recursive for Vector and Tensor which call
get_type_size_bytes. Negligible cost compared to subsequent allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read on type metadata.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_type_alignment" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if type pointer is valid
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get type discriminant
    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)

    Note: Primitive type - alignment is equal to size
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Return get_type_size_bytes(type)
    End If

    Note: FixedPoint type - align to byte boundary
    If discriminant is equal to 1:
        Return get_type_size_bytes(type)
    End If

    Note: Vector type - align to vector size (often 16 bytes for SIMD)
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Let vector_size be get_type_size_bytes(type)

        Note: Clamp to 16-byte max alignment (common hardware limit)
        If vector_size is greater than 16:
            Return 16
        End If

        Return vector_size
    End If

    Note: Matrix type - align to row size
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Let element_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let cols be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 24)

        Let element_size be get_type_size_bytes(element_type)
        Let row_size be element_size multiplied by cols

        Note: Align to element size (conservative)
        Return element_size
    End If

    Note: Texture type - typically 4-byte aligned
    If discriminant is equal to 4:
        Return 4
    End If

    Note: Tensor type - align to element size
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Set element_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Set element_size to get_type_size_bytes(element_type)
        Return element_size
    End If

    Note: Unknown type
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
types_compatible checks if two types can be used interchangeably.
Compatibility rules:
- Exact match: always compatible
- Primitive types: same kind only (no implicit Int32-to-Float32)
- Fixed-point: same bit widths
- Vectors: same element type and size
- Matrices: same element type and dimensions
- Textures: same format and dimensions
- Tensors: same element type and shape
No implicit conversions - accelerators require explicit type conversions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 if either input is null. Returns 1 immediately when pointers are
identical. Reads both discriminants and returns 0 if they differ. For
matching discriminants, runs the variant-specific check: Primitive compares
kind; FixedPoint compares total_bits and fractional_bits; Vector requires
size equality plus a recursive types_compatible on element types; Matrix
requires rows and cols equality plus a recursive check on elements; Texture
compares format and dimensions; Tensor recursively checks element types and
then verifies shape lengths and per-dimension equality via List.get loop.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(rank) for Tensor due to shape walk; O(1) for Primitive/FixedPoint/Texture;
recursive for Vector/Matrix/Tensor element type comparison. Recursion depth
equals type nesting (typically 1-2).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; no mutation, no allocation. False rejection is the safe default
on any mismatch.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "types_compatible" that takes type1 as Integer, type2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Null check
    If type1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Same pointer - definitely compatible
    If type1 is equal to type2:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Get discriminants
    Let disc1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 0)
    Let disc2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 0)

    Note: Different variants - incompatible
    If disc1 is not equal to disc2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Primitive types - check kind matches
    If disc1 is equal to 0:
        Let kind1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Let kind2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)

        If kind1 is equal to kind2:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: FixedPoint types - check bit widths match
    If disc1 is equal to 1:
        Let total1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Let total2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)
        Let frac1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 16)
        Let frac2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 16)

        If total1 is equal to total2:
            If frac1 is equal to frac2:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Vector types - check element type and size match
    If disc1 is equal to 2:
        Let elem1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Let elem2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)
        Let size1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 16)
        Let size2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 16)

        If size1 is not equal to size2:
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Recursively check element types
        Return types_compatible(elem1, elem2)
    End If

    Note: Matrix types - check element type and dimensions match
    If disc1 is equal to 3:
        Set elem1 to Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Set elem2 to Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)
        Let rows1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 16)
        Let rows2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 16)
        Let cols1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 24)
        Let cols2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 24)

        If rows1 is not equal to rows2:
            Return 0
        End If
        If cols1 is not equal to cols2:
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Recursively check element types
        Return types_compatible(elem1, elem2)
    End If

    Note: Texture types - check format and dimensions match
    If disc1 is equal to 4:
        Let format1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Let format2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)
        Let dims1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 16)
        Let dims2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 16)

        If format1 is equal to format2:
            If dims1 is equal to dims2:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Tensor types - check element type and shape match
    If disc1 is equal to 5:
        Set elem1 to Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 8)
        Set elem2 to Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 8)
        Let shape1 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type1, 16)
        Let shape2 be Layout.memory_get_int64(type2, 16)

        Note: Check element types compatible
        Let elem_compat be types_compatible(elem1, elem2)
        If elem_compat is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Check shapes match (same length and all dimensions equal)
        Let len1 be List.length(shape1)
        Let len2 be List.length(shape2)

        If len1 is not equal to len2:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let i be 0
        While i is less than len1:
            Let dim1 be List.get(shape1, i)
            Let dim2 be List.get(shape2, i)

            If dim1 is not equal to dim2:
                Return 0
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Unknown type variant
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
type_to_string generates human-readable string representation of BifrostType.
Essential for debugging, error messages, and graph visualization.
Handles all type variants - primitives produce names like "Int32"/"Float64",
composite variants produce their tag-name short form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "null" for null type. Reads discriminant. For Primitive (0) reads
kind and returns the matched scalar name via StringCore.string_duplicate;
for FixedPoint/Vector/Matrix/Texture/Tensor returns the variant tag string.
Unknown discriminants return "Unknown".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) per call plus one string allocation. Diagnostic-only path; safe to
batch in dump routines.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; returns a freshly duplicated String owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "type_to_string" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("null")
    End If

    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)

    Note: Primitive type
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)

        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT8:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Int8")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT16:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Int16")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT32:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Int32")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_INT64:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Int64")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT8:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("UInt8")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT16:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("UInt16")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT32:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("UInt32")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_UINT64:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("UInt64")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT16:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Float16")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT32:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Float32")
        End If
        If kind is equal to BIFROST_FLOAT64:
            Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Float64")
        End If

        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Primitive(unknown)")
    End If

    Note: FixedPoint type
    If discriminant is equal to 1:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("FixedPoint")
    End If

    Note: Vector type
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Vector")
    End If

    Note: Matrix type
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Matrix")
    End If

    Note: Texture type
    If discriminant is equal to 4:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Texture")
    End If

    Note: Tensor type
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Tensor")
    End If

    Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Unknown")
End Process

@Reasoning
clone_type creates a deep copy of a BifrostType including nested element
types and shape lists. Graph transformations (clone_graph, fuse_nodes) need
independent type instances so mutations on one graph don't reach the other.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null type. Reads discriminant and recurses by variant:
Primitive re-allocates via create_primitive_type(kind); FixedPoint via
create_fixed_point_type(total, frac); Vector recurses on element_type then
calls create_vector_type with the cloned element and the same size; Matrix
recurses on element and reuses rows/cols via create_matrix_type; Texture
clones format+dimensions; Tensor recurses on element and walks the shape
list to build a fresh shape List with the same dimensions, then calls
create_tensor_type.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(rank + nesting) - one allocation per recursive level, plus shape list copy
for Tensor.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Allocates new heap memory at each level; returned type is fully
caller-owned and independent of the source.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "clone_type" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)

    Note: Primitive type - simple copy
    If discriminant is equal to 0:
        Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Return create_primitive_type(kind)
    End If

    Note: FixedPoint type
    If discriminant is equal to 1:
        Let total_bits be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let frac_bits be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Return create_fixed_point_type(total_bits, frac_bits)
    End If

    Note: Vector type - recursively clone element type
    If discriminant is equal to 2:
        Let elem_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let size be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Let elem_clone be clone_type(elem_type)
        Return create_vector_type(elem_clone, size)
    End If

    Note: Matrix type - recursively clone element type
    If discriminant is equal to 3:
        Set elem_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let rows be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Let cols be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 24)
        Set elem_clone to clone_type(elem_type)
        Return create_matrix_type(elem_clone, rows, cols)
    End If

    Note: Texture type
    If discriminant is equal to 4:
        Let format be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let dims be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Return create_texture_type(format, dims)
    End If

    Note: Tensor type - recursively clone element type and shape list
    If discriminant is equal to 5:
        Set elem_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 8)
        Let shape be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 16)
        Set elem_clone to clone_type(elem_type)

        Note: Clone shape list
        Let shape_clone be List.create()
        Let len be List.length(shape)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than len:
            Let dim be List.get(shape, i)
            List.append(shape_clone, dim)
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return create_tensor_type(elem_clone, shape_clone)
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
destroy_type is reserved for future manual memory management. Runa's tier-3
OWNED-HEAP semantics currently rely on graph teardown to reclaim type
storage, so an explicit deallocator is a no-op. The signature is preserved
so when Runa adds explicit deallocation this routine can be wired up
without API changes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 unconditionally - placeholder for future manual deallocation.
The body is intentionally minimal until per-tier deallocation lands.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No-op; no side effects.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_type" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: In production Runa with GC, explicit deallocation unnecessary
    Note: This function reserved for future manual memory management
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Type classification predicates allow pattern-matching code (verifier,
schedule cost models) to branch on type kind without remembering the
discriminant numeric values. Each predicate just reads the discriminant and
compares it to its target tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
is_primitive_type returns 0 for null type; otherwise reads the discriminant
at offset 0 and returns 1 if it equals 0 (Primitive tag), 0 otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one branch plus one 64-bit load.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "is_primitive_type" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)
    If disc is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Symmetric to is_primitive_type for the Vector tag (discriminant 2).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
