End Process

@Reasoning
Symmetric to is_primitive_type for the Matrix tag (discriminant 3).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null type; otherwise returns 1 if the discriminant equals 3.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "is_matrix_type" that takes type as Integer returns Integer:
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(type, 0)
    If disc is equal to 3:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OpKind Utility Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
opkind_to_string converts OpKind to human-readable string.
Essential for debugging, error messages, and DOT graph generation. A linear
If-cascade is used because Match on enums is not available across the
bootstrap compiler chain - explicit discriminant compares are stable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads the OpKind discriminant at offset 0, then runs a long If-cascade
mapping discriminants 0..41 plus 67..69 to their canonical operator names
(Add, MatrixMultiply, FFT, ReLU, Reduce*, Load, Store, Pad, Tile, Reshape,
etc.). Each match returns StringCore.string_duplicate of the literal name.
Unknown discriminants return "UnknownOperation".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(n) where n is the number of OpKind variants (~45 today). Diagnostic only;
not on the hot path. Each match allocates a duplicated String.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; allocates fresh strings owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "opkind_to_string" that takes opkind as OpKind returns Integer:
    Note: Match on OpKind discriminant and return corresponding string
    Note: OpKind is variant type, read discriminant at offset 0
    Let opkind_disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(opkind, 0)

    Note: Arithmetic operations (0-5)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 0:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Add")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 1:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Subtract")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 2:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Multiply")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 3:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Divide")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 4:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Modulo")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 5:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Negate")
    End If

    Note: Matrix operations (6-9)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 6:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("MatrixMultiply")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 7:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("MatrixAdd")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 8:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("MatrixTranspose")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 9:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("MatrixInverse")
    End If

    Note: Vector operations (10-12)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 10:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("VectorDot")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 11:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("VectorCross")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 12:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("VectorNorm")
    End If

    Note: Convolution operations (13-14)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 13:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Convolve2D")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 14:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Convolve3D")
    End If

    Note: Signal processing operations (15-19)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 15:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("FFT")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 16:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("IFFT")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 17:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("FIR_Filter")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 18:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("IIR_Filter")
    End If

    Note: Image processing operations (19-24)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 19:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Blur")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 20:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Sharpen")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 21:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("EdgeDetect")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 22:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ColorConvert")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 23:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Resize")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 24:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Rotate")
    End If

    Note: Activation functions (25-28)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 25:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ReLU")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 26:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Sigmoid")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 27:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Tanh")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 28:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Softmax")
    End If

    Note: Neural network layers (29-32)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 29:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("BatchNorm")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 30:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("LayerNorm")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 31:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ConvLayer")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 32:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("PoolingLayer")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 33:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("FullyConnected")
    End If

    Note: Memory operations (34-37)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 34:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Load")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 35:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Store")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 36:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("LoadTexture")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 37:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("StoreTexture")
    End If

    Note: Reduction operations (38-41)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 38:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ReduceSum")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 39:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ReduceMax")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 40:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ReduceMin")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 41:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("ReduceMean")
    End If

    Note: Layout transformation operations (67-69)
    Note: Pad: tensor padding for alignment/cache-line boundaries
    Note: Tile: tensor restructure into tile-major order for cache locality
    Note: Reshape: generic shape change including AoS<->SoA layout flips
    If opkind_disc is equal to 67:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Pad")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 68:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Tile")
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 69:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Reshape")
    End If

    Note: Default for unknown operations
    Return StringCore.string_duplicate("UnknownOperation")
End Process

@Reasoning
Operation classification predicates let fusion / scheduling / cost passes
branch on op category without remembering the discriminant ranges. Each
predicate inspects the OpKind discriminant and tests the appropriate range.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
opkind_is_arithmetic reads the OpKind discriminant. Returns 1 if it falls
in [0..5] (Add, Subtract, Multiply, Divide, Modulo, Negate), 0 otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "opkind_is_arithmetic" that takes opkind as OpKind returns Integer:
    Note: Check if operation is basic arithmetic (Add, Subtract, Multiply, Divide, Modulo, Negate)
    Let opkind_disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(opkind, 0)

    Note: Arithmetic operations have discriminants 0-5
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 0:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 5:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Tests whether an OpKind is a matrix/vector operation that should be
considered by GEMM/BLAS-routing passes.
