Tests whether an OpKind is a DSP/conv/filter operation routable to
cuFFT/MIOpen-style library backends.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads the OpKind discriminant. Returns 1 if it falls in [13..18]
(Convolve2D, Convolve3D, FFT, IFFT, FIR_Filter, IIR_Filter), 0 otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "opkind_is_signal_processing" that takes opkind as OpKind returns Integer:
    Note: Check if operation is FFT, convolution, filter (discriminants 13-18)
    Note: Convolve2D, Convolve3D, FFT, IFFT, FIR_Filter, IIR_Filter
    Let opkind_disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(opkind, 0)

    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 13:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 18:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
opkind_input_count returns the canonical arity (input operand count) for
each OpKind. Critical for graph construction validation and arity checking;
mismatched arity at lowering time is a hard graph error. Example arities:
Add=2, MatrixMultiply=2, ReLU=1, Convolve2D=3 (input, kernel, bias).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads the OpKind discriminant at offset 0 and runs a per-arity If-cascade:
- 1 input for Negate, VectorNorm, ReLU, Sigmoid, Tanh, Softmax, BatchNorm,
  LayerNorm, Blur, Sharpen, EdgeDetect, ColorConvert, Resize, Rotate,
  MatrixTranspose, MatrixInverse, FFT, IFFT, Load, LoadTexture, ReduceSum,
  ReduceMax, ReduceMin, ReduceMean, Not, BitwiseNot, Cast, Bitcast,
  FloatToInt, IntToFloat, Pad, Tile, Reshape, FIR_Filter, IIR_Filter.
- 3 inputs for Convolve2D, Convolve3D, ConvLayer, PoolingLayer,
  FullyConnected, Select, Clamp, Mix, SmoothStep.
- 2 inputs (default) for all remaining binary ops (Add, Sub, Mul, Div, Mod,
  MatrixMultiply, MatrixAdd, VectorDot, VectorCross, Store, StoreTexture,
  comparisons 42-47, logical 48-50, bitwise binary 52-54, shifts 56-57,
  Step=65).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) with a bounded number of compares (<= ~20). Tight - not a hot path
but cheap enough to call per node during validation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read; no mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "opkind_input_count" that takes opkind as OpKind returns Integer:
    Let opkind_disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(opkind, 0)

    Note: Unary operations (single operand)
    Note: Negate=5
    If opkind_disc is equal to 5:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MatrixTranspose=8, MatrixInverse=9, VectorNorm=12
    If opkind_disc is equal to 8:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 9:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 12:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: FFT=15, IFFT=16, FIR_Filter=17, IIR_Filter=18
    If opkind_disc is equal to 15:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 16:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 17:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 18:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Image processing 1-input ops: Blur=19, Sharpen=20, EdgeDetect=21, ColorConvert=22, Resize=23, Rotate=24
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 19:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 24:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Activation/normalization 1-input ops: ReLU=25, Sigmoid=26, Tanh=27, Softmax=28, BatchNorm=29, LayerNorm=30
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 25:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 30:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Load=34, LoadTexture=36 - single-input (address)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 34:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 36:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Reductions all take a single tensor: ReduceSum=38, ReduceMax=39, ReduceMin=40, ReduceMean=41
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 38:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 41:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Not=51, BitwiseNot=55 - unary logical/bitwise
    If opkind_disc is equal to 51:
        Return 1
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 55:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Type conversions: Cast=58, Bitcast=59, FloatToInt=60, IntToFloat=61
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 58:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 61:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Layout transformation operations: Pad=67, Tile=68, Reshape=69 - single tensor input
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 67:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 69:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Ternary operations
    Note: Convolve2D=13, Convolve3D=14 take (input, kernel, bias)
    If opkind_disc is equal to 13:
        Return 3
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 14:
        Return 3
    End If

    Note: ConvLayer=31, PoolingLayer=32, FullyConnected=33 take (input, weights, bias)
    If opkind_disc is greater than or equal to 31:
        If opkind_disc is less than or equal to 33:
            Return 3
        End If
    End If

    Note: Select=62, Clamp=63, Mix=64, SmoothStep=66 - ternary
    If opkind_disc is equal to 62:
        Return 3
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 63:
        Return 3
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 64:
        Return 3
    End If
    If opkind_disc is equal to 66:
        Return 3
    End If

    Note: Default: all remaining ops are binary (Add, Sub, Mul, Div, Mod,
    Note: MatrixMultiply, MatrixAdd, VectorDot, VectorCross, Store, StoreTexture,
    Note: comparisons 42-47, logical 48-50, bitwise binary 52-54, shifts 56-57, Step=65)
    Return 2
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BifrostNode Management Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
create_constant_node creates node holding compile-time constant value.
Constants enable constant folding, dead code elimination, strength
reduction. Value is stored as a literal integer; the actual value
interpretation (signed/unsigned/float bit pattern) depends on the attached
type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null type. Allocates 24 bytes, writes the Constant
discriminant (0) at offset 0, the value at offset 8, and the type pointer
at offset 16. Returns the node pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one allocation plus three stores. Hot path during constant lowering.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. Type pointer is borrowed; caller must keep the type
live for the node's lifetime.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_constant_node" that takes value as Integer, type as Integer returns Integer:
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostNode structure
    Let node_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(24)

    Note: Set discriminant to Constant (variant 0)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 0, 0)

    Note: Set value and type
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 8, value)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 16, type)

    Return node_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_input_node creates a node representing data flowing into the graph.
Input nodes mark boundaries between CPU and accelerator, or between
different accelerator stages. Memory space (Global / Shared / Local /
Constant) determines where the data physically resides for codegen.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null name or null type. Allocates 32 bytes, writes the Input
discriminant (1) at offset 0, name pointer at offset 8, type pointer at
offset 16, memory_space at offset 24. Returns the node pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) - one allocation plus four stores.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. name and type are borrowed; caller owns them and
must keep them live for the input node's lifetime.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_input_node" that takes name as Integer, type as Integer, memory_space as MemorySpace returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostNode structure
    Let node_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(32)

    Note: Set discriminant to Input (variant 1)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 0, 1)

    Note: Set name, type, and memory space
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 8, name)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 16, type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 24, memory_space)

    Return node_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_output_node creates a node representing data flowing out of the
graph. Output nodes mark where accelerator results return to CPU or
external storage; memory_space dictates the destination tier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Symmetric to create_input_node with discriminant 2 (Output). Returns 0 for
null name or null type. Allocates 32 bytes and writes discriminant, name,
type, memory_space at offsets 0, 8, 16, 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. name and type borrowed; caller owns lifetimes.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_output_node" that takes name as Integer, type as Integer, memory_space as MemorySpace returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostNode structure
    Let node_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(32)

    Note: Set discriminant to Output (variant 2)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 0, 2)

    Note: Set name, type, and memory space
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 8, name)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 16, type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 24, memory_space)

    Return node_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
create_operation_node creates a computational node in the DAG. Operation
nodes transform inputs to outputs using the specified OpKind. The
parallelism model guides backend code generation. Metadata stores optional
annotations (loop bounds, memory hints, profiling data).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null inputs list or null output_type. Allocates 48 bytes,
writes the Operation discriminant (3) at offset 0, op at offset 8, inputs
list pointer at 16, output_type at 24, parallelism at 32. Constructs a
fresh metadata Dictionary at offset 40.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) for the node allocation plus the Dictionary creation. Dictionary
construction dominates because it allocates internal buckets.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
OWNED-HEAP allocation. inputs list and output_type are borrowed (caller
owns lifetimes). Metadata Dictionary is owned by the node and will be freed
with it.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "create_operation_node" that takes op as OpKind, inputs as Integer, output_type as Integer, parallelism as ParallelismKind returns Integer:
    If inputs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If output_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate BifrostNode structure
    Let node_ptr be Layout.memory_allocate(48)

    Note: Set discriminant to Operation (variant 3)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 0, 3)

    Note: Set operation kind, inputs list, output type, parallelism
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 8, op)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 16, inputs)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 24, output_type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 32, parallelism)

    Note: Initialize metadata dictionary
    Let metadata be Dictionary.create()
    Layout.memory_set_int64(node_ptr, 40, metadata)

    Return node_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
add_node_input appends an edge reference to an operation node's input list.
Edge references (not pointers) allow DAG traversal without circular pointer
dependencies between node and edge structs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards the node. Reads discriminant; returns 0 if not 3 (Operation).
Reads the inputs list pointer at offset 16 and appends edge_ref via
List.append. Returns 1 on success.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) amortised List append.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Mutates the node's inputs list (borrowed by the list, owned by the caller
through the node).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "add_node_input" that takes node as Integer, edge_ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check node is Operation variant
    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get inputs list
    Let inputs be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)

    Note: Append edge reference
    List.append(inputs, edge_ref)

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
remove_node_input removes an edge reference from an operation node's input
list. Used during graph transformations that disconnect a producer from a
consumer (e.g. fusion absorbing one of the inputs).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards node; returns 0 if not an Operation. Reads the inputs list and
linearly scans for edge_ref; on match removes via List.remove_at and
returns 1. Returns 0 on miss.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(degree(node)) linear scan plus O(degree) shift on remove_at. Removal is
infrequent so the cost is acceptable.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Mutates the node's inputs list.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "remove_node_input" that takes node as Integer, edge_ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check node is Operation variant
    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get inputs list
    Let inputs be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)

    Note: Find and remove edge reference
    Let len be List.length(inputs)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ref be List.get(inputs, i)
        If ref is equal to edge_ref:
            List.remove_at(inputs, i)
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Pure accessor for the inputs edge-ref list of an Operation node. Returning
0 for non-Operation variants tells callers there is no input slot to walk.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null node or non-Operation discriminant. Otherwise returns
the list pointer stored at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a BORROWED list pointer; mutations affect the node directly.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_node_inputs" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience accessor that combines get_node_inputs with List.length so
verifier/cost-model paths can ask for arity in one call.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Calls get_node_inputs; returns 0 if the result is null, otherwise returns
List.length on the inputs list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_node_input_count" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let inputs be get_node_inputs(node)
    If inputs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return List.length(inputs)
End Process

@Reasoning
set_node_output_type updates an Operation node's output type. Type-inference
passes call this when they refine a generic type into a concrete one.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards node and type; returns 0 on either. Verifies the node is an
Operation discriminant (3); returns 0 otherwise. Writes the new type
pointer at offset 24 and returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Borrowed type pointer; caller must keep it live. The previous type pointer
is overwritten without freeing - if it was owned exclusively by the node,
that storage leaks until graph teardown.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_node_output_type" that takes node as Integer, type as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(node, 24, type)
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Type accessor that handles all four node variants uniformly so the verifier
and edge-type checks can fetch a node's effective output type without
caring about variant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null node. Reads the discriminant; for Constant (0), Input
(1), and Output (2) returns the type field at offset 16; for Operation (3)
returns output_type at offset 24. Unknown discriminants return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_node_output_type" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)

    Note: Constant node - return type field
    If disc is equal to 0:
        Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
    End If

    Note: Input node - return type field
    If disc is equal to 1:
        Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
    End If

    Note: Output node - return type field
    If disc is equal to 2:
        Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
    End If

    Note: Operation node - return output_type field
    If disc is equal to 3:
        Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 24)
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
set_node_parallelism updates the parallelism model on an Operation node.
The parallelism kind (DataParallel / TaskParallel / Pipeline / etc.)
controls how the backend will lower the operation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards the node and verifies discriminant equals 3 (Operation). Writes
the parallelism value at offset 32 and returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure metadata mutation. Caller is responsible for choosing a parallelism
mode the backend supports.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_node_parallelism" that takes node as Integer, parallelism as ParallelismKind returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(node, 32, parallelism)
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the parallelism kind for an Operation node. Returns DataParallel
as the safe default for null or non-Operation nodes so downstream code can
keep its default-DataParallel scheduling assumption.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns DataParallel for null node or non-Operation discriminant; otherwise
reads the ParallelismKind value from offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_node_parallelism" that takes node as Integer returns ParallelismKind:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return DataParallel
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return DataParallel
    End If

    Return Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 32)
End Process

@Reasoning
Stores a key-value annotation on an Operation node's metadata dict.
Examples: loop bounds, memory hints, profiling counts, optimization flags
consumed by later passes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards node and key. Verifies discriminant is 3. Reads the metadata
Dict pointer at offset 40 and calls Dictionary.set(key, value). Returns 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) amortised Dict set.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Mutates the node's metadata Dict. Key/value pointers are borrowed; the Dict
captures both. Caller must keep them live or copy them in.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "set_node_metadata" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let metadata be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 40)
    Dictionary.set(metadata, key, value)
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Retrieves a metadata value by key from an Operation node. Returns 0 for
missing keys so passes can use it as a sparse map.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards node and key. Verifies Operation discriminant. Reads the
metadata Dict and returns Dictionary.get(key); 0 on miss.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) amortised hashed lookup.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returned value is borrowed from the Dict; caller must not free it.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_node_metadata" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let metadata be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 40)
    Return Dictionary.get(metadata, key)
End Process

@Reasoning
Existence test for a metadata key. Avoids forcing callers to treat a 0 from
get_node_metadata as ambiguous (could mean "missing" or "stored zero").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Null-guards node and key, verifies Operation discriminant, reads the
metadata Dict, calls Dictionary.get(key) and returns 1 if the result is
non-zero, 0 otherwise. Note: stored-zero values cannot be distinguished
from missing by this routine; callers needing zero-as-value should use
Dictionary.has_key directly.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) hashed lookup.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "has_node_metadata" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is not equal to 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let metadata be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 40)
    Let value be Dictionary.get(metadata, key)
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Per-node type validation: ensures Operation nodes have the right number of
inputs for their OpKind (arity check) and that Constant/Input/Output nodes
trivially validate. Full edge-level type-compatibility validation lives in
validate_graph because it needs edge information not visible here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null node. Reads discriminant. For Constant/Input/Output
(disc < 3) returns 1 (trivially valid). For Operation (disc == 3) reads
op kind and inputs list, compares List.length(inputs) to
opkind_input_count(op); returns 0 on mismatch, 1 otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) plus the cost of opkind_input_count (bounded compares).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "validate_node_types" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)

    Note: Constant, Input, Output nodes - always valid (no input constraints)
    If disc is less than 3:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Operation node - validate inputs match expected types
    If disc is equal to 3:
        Note: Get operation kind and inputs
        Let op be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 8)
        Let inputs be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
        Let input_count be List.length(inputs)

        Note: Check input count matches operation arity
        Let expected_count be opkind_input_count(op)
        If input_count is not equal to expected_count:
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Additional type checking deferred to graph validation
        Note: (requires edge information not available at node level)
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Stringifies a node's variant tag for diagnostic dumps. Detailed per-variant
fields (constant value, input name, op kind) are dumped at the graph level
by graph_to_string; this routine intentionally produces the short form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns "null" for null node. Reads discriminant; returns
StringCore.string_duplicate of "Constant" / "Input" / "Output" / "Operation"
for discriminants 0..3, "Unknown" otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a freshly duplicated String owned by caller.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "node_to_string" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("null")
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)

    If disc is equal to 0:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Constant")
    End If
    If disc is equal to 1:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Input")
    End If
    If disc is equal to 2:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Output")
    End If
    If disc is equal to 3:
        Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Operation")
    End If

    Return StringCore.string_duplicate("Unknown")
End Process

@Reasoning
clone_node creates a deep copy of any node variant for graph
transformations that need an independent node (e.g. clone_graph). The
attached type is cloned recursively; input lists are duplicated.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null node. Reads discriminant. For Constant (0) reads value
and type, clones the type, and constructs via create_constant_node. For
Input (1) and Output (2) reads name, type, memory_space, clones the type,
and constructs via create_input_node / create_output_node. For Operation
(3) reads op, inputs list, output_type, parallelism, walks the inputs and
appends every edge_ref into a fresh inputs_clone list, clones output_type,
and constructs via create_operation_node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(inputs.length + type-nesting). The input-list clone is the dominant cost
for fan-in heavy nodes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Allocates a fresh node, type clone, and (for Operation) a fresh inputs
list. Returned node is independent of the source; metadata Dict is NOT
copied (the Operation clone has its own freshly created metadata Dict, not
a copy of the source's).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "clone_node" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)

    Note: Constant node
    If disc is equal to 0:
        Let value be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 8)
        Let type be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
        Let type_clone be clone_type(type)
        Return create_constant_node(value, type_clone)
    End If

    Note: Input node
    If disc is equal to 1:
        Let name be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 8)
        Set type to Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
        Let mem_space be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 24)
        Set type_clone to clone_type(type)
        Return create_input_node(name, type_clone, mem_space)
    End If

    Note: Output node
    If disc is equal to 2:
        Set name to Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 8)
        Set type to Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
        Set mem_space to Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 24)
        Set type_clone to clone_type(type)
        Return create_output_node(name, type_clone, mem_space)
    End If

    Note: Operation node
    If disc is equal to 3:
        Let op be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 8)
        Let inputs be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 16)
        Let output_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 24)
        Let parallelism be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 32)

        Note: Clone inputs list
        Let inputs_clone be List.create()
        Let len be List.length(inputs)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than len:
            Let edge_ref be List.get(inputs, i)
            List.append(inputs_clone, edge_ref)
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Set type_clone to clone_type(output_type)
        Return create_operation_node(op, inputs_clone, type_clone, parallelism)
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
destroy_node is the per-node companion to destroy_type. Reserved for future
manual deallocation; today the GC reclaims node memory at graph teardown.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 unconditionally - no-op until manual deallocation lands.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No-op.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_node" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Runa GC handles deallocation automatically
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Predicate for the Constant node variant. Used by constant-folding passes
and by the DCE pass to identify literal sources.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 0 for null node; otherwise reads the discriminant at offset 0 and
returns 1 if it equals 0 (Constant tag), 0 otherwise.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure read.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "is_node_constant" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let disc be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, 0)
    If disc is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
